!! Transforms

A //transform// is a named function that reshapes a token's value before substitution.  The plugin ships a handful of built-ins and lets you add your own.

The leaf sections below come from the [[Usage guide|$:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/usage]]'s transform chapters (transcluded here, so there's one source of truth for the content).  In the Usage guide they're presented as §6 and §8; this guide drops the numbering and gathers them as a single read.

---

!! Template tokens and transforms

Tokens are the workhorse of bindings.  Their grammar is:

```
{{ path [|transform]* }}
```

That is: a path, optionally followed by one or more `|transform` pipes.

